# xregion

## Intro

A very simple tool for X, which lets you select a region of the screen
in a way similar to "scrot -s", and then prints out its coordinates.

## Usage

xregion [-h] [-g] [-w] [-a]

-a print short help
-g print coordinates as XxY+W+H
-w force using selected window instead of region
-a use absolute coordinates instead of width and height ```

see examples/ for sample applications

## Install/Uninstall

  # make install
  # make uninstall
